commitResults.messageBody:
Renamed bot to APleaseBot
Changed text printout

Added Task class
Abstracted some functions to Task class
Implemented functionality to mark tasks as done and not done
Left comments for error catching later

Added various types of tasks: ToDo, Deadline and Event
String representation of the tasks have been implemented within the Task object
Added a catch for unrecognised commands in the else block. Responds with "What?"

* Error catching complete for implemented functions
* Created error classes for handling different type
  of errors amde by the user

* Reworked whole program to follow OOP principles better
* Encapsulated all commands into their own classes
  extending from Commands class
* Created a Parser class to replace the if-else block
  passes the input to the appropriate commands after

* Added delete command
* Updated TaskList Class to use Java ArrayList instead of Array[100]

* Added in test cases into input.txt file
* Added in expected outcome into EXPECTED.TXT file
* Edited directory and bot file name in runtest.sh file
* Removed spaces after the "Got it. I've added this task:\n"
  lines in task commands

* Added a new class ByeCommand to write the changes on taskList
  to the txt file
* Edited the APleaseBot.java file to load the txt file into
  taskList
* Remaining edits were from trying different methods of
  implementation

* Add ability for bot to recognise datetime format
* Create TimeFormatter class to handle the formatting of
  String to LocalDateTime and LocalDateTime to display
  format

* Only had to make the Storage and UI classes
* Edited my Parser and TaskList class to allow for behaviour more
  similar to the example code file in the website

* Move all java files into appropriate package folders
* Include package line for all files
* Include appropriate package imports for all files
